def examine_data(df):
    for name in df.columns:
        print('---------')
        print(df[name].dtype)
        if df[name].dtype is np.dtype('object'):
            print(df[name].value_counts())
            print('Name:',name)

for i in ['job','marital','education','default','housing','loan','contact','month','poutcome','Target']:
    df[i] = le.fit_transform(df[i])
        
    #print(dict(zip(i,df[i].items())))
    print(f'{i}:', dict(zip(le.classes_, range(len(le.classes_)))))

Importing the metrics and ClassfifcationReport library¶

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix,recall_score,precision_score,f1_score,roc_auc_score,accuracy_score,mean_absolute_error
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

from yellowbrick.classifier import ClassificationReport, ROCAUC



    















Creating a function to use the same function and will run the multiple models¶












In [51]:



    


def algorithms(model_selection):
    global model_s 
    model_s = model_selection
    model_s.fit(X_train,y_train)
    global y_predict
    y_predict = model_s.predict(X_test)
    scoring = model_s.score(X_test,y_test)
    
    
    def draw_cm(actual,predicted):
        cm=confusion_matrix(actual,predicted)
        sns.heatmap(cm,annot=True,fmt='.2f',xticklabels=[0,1],yticklabels=[0,1])
        plt.ylabel('Actual')
        plt.xlabel('Predicted')
        plt.show()
    
    print('model_selection:', model_s)
    print()
    print('-----'*20)
    print("Confusion Matrix:")
    print(draw_cm(y_test,y_predict))
    
    
    viz = ClassificationReport(model_s)
    viz.fit(X_train, y_train)
    viz.score(X_test, y_test)
    viz.show()
    
    roc = ROCAUC(model_s)
    roc.fit(X_train,y_train)
    roc.score(X_test,y_test)
    roc.show()

    GBC.loc[row_index, 'F1 Score'] = round(f1_score(y_test, y_predict), 4)
    GBC.loc[row_index, 'ROC AUC Score'] = round(roc_auc_score(y_test, y_predict), 4)
    
    row_index+=1
     
GBC
